FINAL CALL FOR PARTICIPATION=20
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D
Workshop on Semantic Spaces at the Intersection of NLP, Physics and =
Cognitive Science=20
Co-located with QPL-2016=20

Date: 11th June 2016, 09:30-18:00=20
Place: University of Strathclyde, Glasgow, Scotland=20
McCance Building, Room 319=20

The programme is now finalised and available online!
Website: https://sites.google.com/site/semspworkshop =
<https://sites.google.com/site/semspworkshop>=20
General enquiries: slpcs2016@easychair.org =
<mailto:slpcs2016@easychair.org>=20

INVITED SPEAKERS=20
----------------=20
* Hans Briegel, University of Innsbruck - Projective Simulation for =
Learning and Agency=20
* Peter G=C3=A4rdenfors, University of Lund - The Role of Domains in the =
Representation of Word Meaning
* Dominic Widdows, Microsoft - Semantics Spaces: Successes and Goals

SHORT DESCRIPTION=20
-----------------=20
Exploiting the common ground provided by the concept of a vector=20
space, the workshop aims to bring together researchers working=20
at the intersection of NLP, cognitive science, and physics,=20
offering to them an appropriate forum for presenting their uniquely=20
motivated work and ideas. The interplay between these three=20
disciplines will foster theoretically motivated approaches to=20
understanding how meanings of words interact with each other in=20
sentences and discourse, how diagrammatic reasoning  depicts and=20
simplifies this interaction, how language models are determined=20
by input from the world, and how word and sentence meanings=20
interact logically.=20

CONTRIBUTED LONG TALKS=20
----------------------=20
* Daniela Ashoush and Bob Coecke. Dual density operators and=20
   natural language meaning=20
* Josef Bolt, Bob Coecke, Fabrizio Genovese, Martha Lewis,=20
   Dan Marsden and Robin Piedeleu. Interacting Conceptual Spaces=20
* Dimitri Kartsaklis. Coordination in Categorical Compositional=20
   Distributional Semantics=20
* Mehrnoosh Sadrzadeh. Quantifier Scope in Categorical Compositional=20
   Distributional Semantics=20
* William Zeng and Bob Coecke. Quantum algorithms for compositional=20
   natural language processing=20

CONTRIBUTED SHORT TALKS=20
-----------------------=20
* Stefano Gogioso. A corpus-based toy model for DisCoCat=20
* Stephen McGregor, Matthew Purver and Geraint Wiggins.=20
   Words, Concepts, and the Geometry of Analogy
* John van der Wetering. Entailment Relations on Distributions=20

